getValue

public java.lang.Double getValue(FeatureAttribute attribute)
Get the value of a feature attribute in this vector.

Here is where special "bag" logic is applied such that if the attribute is from a bag of words and this vector has not recorded a value for the attribute, then the "not present" value will be returned. This is intended to exhibit the behavior that words not present are known to be not present as opposed to unknown or uninstantiated. If it is being asked for (because the dictionary knows about it) and this vector doesn't have it, then it is a word known not to be present.

Returns:
the set value, default value, or null if not set.

getExtractionFlag

public java.lang.Boolean getExtractionFlag()
Get the extraction flag from this vector.

The extraction flag allows us to test the status of the features on this vector.

If null, then an extractor has not been run.

If false, then the extractor has been run, but failed.

If true, then the extractor has been run and succeeded.

Returns:
the extractionFlag.

getValuesStrings

public java.lang.String[] getValuesStrings()
Get this instance's feature's values as strings in dictionary order.

If there are no attributes set on this vector, then null will be returned.

Note that values not recorded in this vector for attributes known by the dictionary are also included, but may be null.

getValuesValues

public java.lang.Double[] getValuesValues()
Get this instance's feature's values as doubles in dictionary order.

If there are no attributes set on this vector, then null will be returned.

Note that values not recorded in this vector for attributes known by the dictionary are also included, but may be null.
